{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Place water and yeast in mixing bowl then heat <b>1 min 30 sec\/37°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add spelt flour, white bread flour, oil and salt then mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Knead <b>3 min\/<b>. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl.","Transfer dough to prepared bowl, cover with cling film and leave to rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1-2 hours). Meanwhile, clean and dry mixing bowl then prepare reduction."]},{"title":"Balsamic Reduction","content":["Place vinegar and sugar in mixing bowl then, replace measuring cup with simmering basket, and cook <b>22 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a sterilised jar and set aside."]},{"title":"Topping","content":["Towards the end of resting time, preheat oven to 220°C and grease two large baking trays.","Tip dough out onto a lightly floured work surface and divide into two pieces. Roll each piece into a circle (approx. Ø 30 cm) and place one on each prepared  baking tray.","Spread 2 Tbsp pesto over each pizza then arrange mozzarella, prosciutto and nectarines over the top. Scatter pizzas with fresh thyme leaves then bake for 12-15 minutes (220°C) until crust is lightly golden brown and cheese is melted.","Scatter rocket over the top and drizzle with reserved balsamic reduction before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["220 g water","2 tsp dried instant yeast","200 g spelt flour","200 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for dusting","20 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","1 tsp fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Balsamic Reduction","content":["250 g balsamic vinegar","25 g granulated sugar"]},{"title":"Topping","content":["4 Tbsp red pepper pesto","250 g mozzarella, sliced","6 slices prosciutto, torn in large pieces (approx. 80 g)","2 nectarines, each sliced in 8 segments","4 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","50 g rocket leaves"]}],"id":"r131293","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-nu8d9Q8ro_0\/XZQupk4pd9I\/AAAAAAAAcVo\/tT1GbkSr9